{"type":"user.message","data":{"content":"I'm migrating my MSTest projects from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\nMy repo has a single Directory.Build.props at the root that is imported by\nboth production projects (e.g. `MyApp.csproj`) and test projects (e.g.\n`MyApp.Tests.csproj`). I want to set `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` and the\nMTP runner properties centrally, but I obviously don't want to turn my\nlibrary projects into executables. How do I write the condition in\nDirectory.Build.props so it only applies to the test projects?\n","transformedContent":"<current_datetime>2026-04-28T01:00:44.167Z</current_datetime>\n\nI'm migrating my MSTest projects from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\nMy repo has a single Directory.Build.props at the root that is imported by\nboth production projects (e.g. `MyApp.csproj`) and test projects (e.g.\n`MyApp.Tests.csproj`). I want to set `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` and the\nMTP runner properties centrally, but I obviously don't want to turn my\nlibrary projects into executables. How do I write the condition in\nDirectory.Build.props so it only applies to the test projects?","attachments":[],"interactionId":"b93cc8f5-4e0f-410f-9ed7-8c830f7d5e21"},"id":"c7f0748b-7d80-461a-ab7f-cc12d88a92ea","timestamp":"2026-04-28T01:00:44.167Z","parentId":"341d7801-39c2-4c04-9929-8751257d139d"}
